# @ai-sdk/pixelart

The **PixelArt AI provider** for the [AI SDK](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs) generates pixel-art style images using the [PixelArt AI API](https://api.pixelart.ai).

## Setup

The PixelArt provider is available via the `@ai-sdk/pixelart` module. Install it with:

```bash
npm install @ai-sdk/pixelart
```

## Provider Instance

You can import the default provider instance `pixelArt` from `@ai-sdk/pixelart`:

```ts
import { pixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
```

To create a custom provider instance, use `createPixelArt`:

```ts
import { createPixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';

const pixelArt = createPixelArt({
  apiKey: 'your-api-key', // defaults to PIXELART_API_KEY env variable
});
```

## Image Generation

```ts
import { pixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
import { generateImage } from 'ai';

const { image } = await generateImage({
  model: pixelArt.image('pixelart-standard'),
  prompt: 'A castle on a hill at sunset',
});
```

### Provider Options

You can pass PixelArt-specific options via `providerOptions`:

```ts
import { pixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
import { generateImage } from 'ai';

const { image } = await generateImage({
  model: pixelArt.image('pixelart-pro'),
  prompt: 'A spaceship flying through the galaxy',
  size: '512x512',
  providerOptions: {
    pixelart: {
      style: '8bit',       // 'pixel' | 'retro' | '8bit'
      pixelDensity: 16,    // 1–64, controls pixel block size
    },
  },
});
```

## Model IDs

| Model ID              | Description                              |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `pixelart-standard`   | Balanced quality and speed               |
| `pixelart-pro`        | Higher quality, slower generation        |
| `pixelart-retro`      | Classic retro game aesthetic             |

## Documentation

For full documentation, visit [https://ai-sdk.dev/docs](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs).

